_Remarks_: NODE_PATH and ENTITY_NAME is 'event', as this is the starting (Level 1) node name as per Json where we want to start data processing from.
Starting ROOT_FLAG of each node will be 1, for other fields of that node ROOT_FLAG = 0
We used table synonyms to fill up TABLE_NAME field

OvrAllID' field doesn't exist in Json, but OVR_ALL_ID is primary key of this table which we want to populate with some attribute from its parent node. Please note, the entry in PARENT_COLUMN field must exist in Json and should belong to immidiate parent node.
PARENT_NODE is 'event|1' as 'event' is parent node of 'Abs' and '1' is the starting FIELD_ID of 'event' node
We used <SchemaName>.<TableName> to fill up TABLE_NAME field

Though 'vrsTyp' field comes from Json, but we don't want to load this attribute's data in database. That's why we marked CUR_IND = 'N'. Please note, to load any attribute's data in database CUR_IND must be marked as 'Y'. Else the data won't be loaded in DB.

Though 'as901' node comes from Json, but we don't want to load this node's data in database. That's why we marked TABLE_NAME = 'DUMMY' for the entire node. Please note, if you don't want to load an entire node's data, mark the TABLE_NAME as 'DUMMY'. Please don't leave the field blank.
